215
00:21:40,519 --> 00:21:45,299
was proud of Job at the time, and he was telling the angels, look at my servant Job.

216
00:21:46,099 --> 00:21:52,900
And Satan said, well look at him, he is rich, he has a family, he is not under any pressure,

217
00:21:53,079 --> 00:21:58,759
so why shouldn't he worship you? And God said, okay, I'm going to lend you Job for a while.

218
00:21:59,019 --> 00:22:03,460
Now remember Job is always in God's eye, and Satan has limits where he can go.

219
00:22:03,460 --> 00:22:07,420
So, Satan started to work on Job.

220
00:22:09,019 --> 00:22:14,539
And this is why you see, recall our servant Job, he called his Lord saying, the devil

221
00:22:14,539 --> 00:22:16,960
has afflicted me with disease and suffering.

222
00:22:18,019 --> 00:22:18,859
He knows.

223
00:22:19,099 --> 00:22:19,980
Job knows.

224
00:22:21,380 --> 00:22:26,559
And so, God may lend you to Satan for a while.

225
00:22:26,559 --> 00:22:34,299
And if Satan gets you in his hands, just like when you catch a fish, he's going to gut you.

226
00:22:42,779 --> 00:22:46,359
You must steadfastly persevere, and you cannot flunk a test.

227
00:22:46,559 --> 00:22:51,279
And when you flunk a test, you regress, you start again at square one, square zero.

228
00:22:54,599 --> 00:23:00,579
So, we have to turn to God right now and do two things, first, thank Him for saving the

229
00:23:00,579 --> 00:23:07,940
planet earth because of us, thank Him for guiding us, whatever led our steps to this

230
00:23:07,940 --> 00:23:15,019
place, me and you, this is the greatest blessing that ever happened to you, and we have to

231
00:23:15,019 --> 00:23:15,839
thank God for it.

232
00:23:15,839 --> 00:23:19,400
then we're going to ask God to keep us on the path

233
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:22,140
steadfast, to persevere, no matter what happens

234
00:23:23,120 --> 00:23:25,339
Steadfast, to persevere, la ilaha illallah

235
00:23:25,339 --> 00:23:27,079
nothing will take us away

236
00:23:28,259 --> 00:23:29,140
Natoobu ilallah.

237
00:23:53,180 --> 00:24:00,400
I have been talking in the last khutbahs about situations in the hereafter, actual situations

238
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:01,519
in the hereafter.

239
00:24:02,159 --> 00:24:07,839
And in my last khutbah I talked to you about the verse that you saw here, where God gathers

240
00:24:07,839 --> 00:24:12,259
people and asks them, Where are your idols to help you?, and they say, by God our Lord we

241
00:24:12,259 --> 00:24:13,299
were not idol worshipers.

242
00:24:14,019 --> 00:24:19,599
It's an actual situation where people are not aware now, they swear to you they are

243
00:24:19,599 --> 00:24:20,460
not idol worshippers.

244
00:24:20,980 --> 00:24:26,599
And they swear then on the Day of Judgment that they are not idol worshippers, they are

245
00:24:26,599 --> 00:24:26,960
not aware.

246
00:24:27,559 --> 00:24:34,000
And I went through the signs of idol worship, that they cannot stand to talk about God

247
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:40,900
alone, they cannot quote the Quran alone, 17:45, and they cannot accept what God says

248
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:41,400
in the Quran.

249
00:24:41,400 --> 00:24:47,059
When He said Muhammad was astray and was guided, I have read the translation for you.

250
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:54,099
Incredible wasn't it? They changed his straying into a virtue.

251
00:24:54,440 --> 00:24:59,220
He was lost in love for this world, for its people, whatever the great distraction was.

252
00:24:59,599 --> 00:25:03,720
And I will connect that situation with a specific situation in the hereafter.

253
00:25:13,319 --> 00:25:18,319
This was a human being. This was a human being.

254
00:25:20,620 --> 00:25:22,119
Someday I'm going to look like this.

255
00:25:27,500 --> 00:25:28,880
Someday you'll look like this.

256
00:25:29,279 --> 00:25:32,900
Just imagine handsome Abdullah is going to look like this someday.

257
00:25:37,379 --> 00:25:39,420
Beautiful Rahimah will look like this, someday.

258
00:25:42,779 --> 00:25:45,220
For some people, like myself, this is an improvement.

259
00:25:49,019 --> 00:25:50,700
This person had beautiful teeth.

260
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:55,799
This was a person that lived on earth, just like we are now.

261
00:25:57,059 --> 00:26:01,319
And you can imagine how much time was spent just for this eating.

262
00:26:02,639 --> 00:26:09,319
And this happens to be a female, and can you imagine how many times she chewed food?

263
00:26:12,119 --> 00:26:16,420
You can look, you can see the teeth, how much food this person had to eat.

264
00:26:18,839 --> 00:26:25,599
She probably worked, she had a boss, she had lots of friends.

265
00:26:29,499 --> 00:26:31,920
She drove a car, maybe.

266
00:26:33,700 --> 00:26:37,539
She had fights with her friends, and relatives.

267
00:26:37,980 --> 00:26:38,920
She had plans.

268
00:26:44,180 --> 00:26:45,420
She made love.

269
00:26:45,420 --> 00:26:57,319
Look down. See, I don't know how many miles she walked. This was a person. You're going to be

270
00:26:57,319 --> 00:27:06,160
like this. Your body will be like this. Now, I want to draw your attention to God's design.

271
00:27:06,339 --> 00:27:14,519
Imagine God designing the human skull, just the skull. Imagine, just for the sake of understanding,

272
00:27:14,519 --> 00:27:21,599
Imagine God as a great architect, chairman of the board at a big desk, designing the human skull.

273
00:27:22,579 --> 00:27:28,380
And God says, "I'm going to leave two openings for the eyes, because this human being will have two eyes."

274
00:27:29,519 --> 00:27:33,119
And there has to be an opening in here for the nose, to breathe.

275
00:27:34,399 --> 00:27:43,119
Here and here. Now, the eyes go in these holes, so God said, "I'm going to make these eye sockets."

276
00:27:43,799 --> 00:27:50,119
And if you look in there, you see very tiny holes inside for the optic nerve to go through to the brain.

277
00:27:55,459 --> 00:28:01,440
And if you look in here, you see the sinus passages.

278
00:28:03,240 --> 00:28:08,539
And the teeth are something else, the design of the teeth, the cutters and the grinders.

279
00:28:12,059 --> 00:28:15,160
An opening for the ear, you see the small opening on the side?

280
00:28:15,319 --> 00:28:22,519
From the ear hole here, it leads to the auditory nerve, on to the brain.

281
00:28:23,079 --> 00:28:27,160
And this is very hard, you know, to protect the brain.

282
00:28:27,539 --> 00:28:30,839
God put the brain inside this case.

283
00:28:31,979 --> 00:28:37,359
Now, God didn't put these things on there, the strings. Those have been put there.

284
00:28:40,420 --> 00:28:44,420
My goodness, see, this is very tough. It's made of a number of layers, you can see the layers.

285
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:49,940
This was a human being, look what we're doing with her.

286
00:28:51,680 --> 00:28:56,420
The brain is protected in fluid, which is very important.

287
00:28:56,900 --> 00:29:01,380
I can see the opening at the bottom of the skull, for the spine.

288
00:29:02,839 --> 00:29:05,640
Everything in the body is controlled from here.

289
00:29:13,359 --> 00:29:16,779
Now I want to move on to a situation in the hereafter.

290
00:29:18,059 --> 00:29:21,920
This person, this was the garment.

291
00:29:24,439 --> 00:29:37,759
This person was buried. But the person herself is asleep. She doesn't know that she died.

292
00:29:55,359 --> 00:30:02,819
Then this person, let us say she is an average Christian, or an average Muslim, or an average

293
00:30:02,819 --> 00:30:10,579
Jew, who fell into idolatry, when she gets up, she would rise then.

294
00:30:11,420 --> 00:30:17,740
Resurrection. All the people who ever existed on earth will be up on this earth,

295
00:30:18,900 --> 00:30:19,380
resurrected.

296
00:30:20,759 --> 00:30:32,140
And this Methodist says, "My God, it's true! Wow, everything we heard is true! We see the

297
00:30:32,140 --> 00:30:32,460
resurrection."

298
00:30:36,340 --> 00:30:38,619
I didn't pay attention to this day.

299
00:30:40,380 --> 00:30:42,279
Look at that big person over there.

300
00:30:44,380 --> 00:30:46,500
See? They have a small sign.

301
00:30:49,859 --> 00:30:54,180
And she would go to this great person and she would say, how did you get like that?

302
00:30:55,660 --> 00:30:00,460
And he would say, "Well, for one thing, I never missed breakfast."

303
00:31:01,099 --> 00:31:02,180
It never fails.

304
00:31:05,660 --> 00:31:08,240
And she would say, "Well, I didn't miss breakfast either.

305
00:31:09,420 --> 00:31:12,519
You know, eggs and bread."

306
00:31:14,420 --> 00:31:20,420
And the other fellow was saying, "Yeah, but were you purifying your garment? You didn't keep..."

307
00:31:20,559 --> 00:31:21,759
How was my acting, by the way?

308
00:31:23,220 --> 00:31:24,240
Not bad, either.

309
00:31:26,180 --> 00:31:28,420
I should have also the voice tone, you know.

310
00:31:28,579 --> 00:31:29,799
"Oh, what made you do that?"

311
00:31:29,920 --> 00:31:30,319
"I don't know."

312
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:31,400
Well.

313
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:35,940
Just don't call Hollywood.

314
00:31:36,039 --> 00:31:37,680
I'm not in a position to do that.

315
00:31:38,940 --> 00:31:41,400
I don't want the director bugging me, you know.

316
00:31:44,039 --> 00:31:48,380
But this is an actual situation where people will be in different, different sizes.

317
00:31:49,420 --> 00:31:51,960
And then she will ask, "What is going to happen now?"

318
00:31:52,940 --> 00:31:59,640
He will say, "Well, the next thing that will happen is God will come to this earth.

319
00:32:00,339 --> 00:32:05,299
And the energy associated with God is equivalent to millions of hydrogen bombs.

320
00:32:07,859 --> 00:32:13,420
If you imagine this earth with a million hydrogen bombs falling on it, what would happen?

321
00:32:13,740 --> 00:32:15,599
See, this is why God taught us nuclear science.

322
00:32:16,480 --> 00:32:20,619
This is why God let us invent hydrogen bombs.

323
00:32:20,900 --> 00:32:24,140
So we can understand what happens when heat comes.

324
00:32:24,579 --> 00:32:25,819
This is what the Quran says."

325
00:32:30,100 --> 00:32:35,819
And the big person will go on and say, "When God comes, you cannot stand the Lord.

326
00:32:36,259 --> 00:32:40,819
The energy associated with God is equivalent to millions of hydrogen bombs.

327
00:32:41,940 --> 00:32:45,220
And when God comes, this whole earth is going to shatter into pieces.

328
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:49,039
Like a million hydrogen bombs hit it.

329
00:32:49,980 --> 00:32:53,480
The stars will crash and disintegrate,

330
00:32:54,539 --> 00:32:57,200
and you are going to be in bad trouble.

331
00:32:57,200 --> 00:32:59,079
You cannot stand the presence of God.

332
00:33:01,539 --> 00:33:03,339
So, child, then what will you do?"

333
00:33:04,619 --> 00:33:06,740
I say, "I'm going to feed on that energy.

334
00:33:06,740 --> 00:33:07,980
I'm going to enjoy it immensely.

335
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:10,460
And as soon as God comes,

336
00:33:10,460 --> 00:33:11,619
we're going to be stratified

337
00:33:12,379 --> 00:33:13,180
into ranks.

338
00:33:14,279 --> 00:33:15,559
You will have to run away

339
00:33:17,559 --> 00:33:18,220
to Hell."

340
00:33:21,139 --> 00:33:22,660
This will be actual conversation.

341
00:33:25,419 --> 00:33:29,799
And she will say, "Well, I'm going to run to Jesus and see if he can help me.

342
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:35,940
Because I believe in Jesus."

343
00:33:38,920 --> 00:33:44,079
And she may go up to Jesus, and he would say, "I'm in deep trouble myself.

344
00:33:44,359 --> 00:33:45,039
I have my own troubles.

345
00:33:45,180 --> 00:33:49,200
You know, all that has happened right now is the initial resurrection has taken place.

346
00:33:50,460 --> 00:33:51,579
I can't help you.

347
00:33:53,759 --> 00:33:57,940
God is the one who created you, God is the one who provided for you, God is the one who

348
00:33:57,940 --> 00:34:04,259
terminated your life, God is the one who resurrected you, and God is the one who will hold you

349
00:34:04,259 --> 00:34:05,980
to account, hold you to account."

350
00:34:07,759 --> 00:34:11,639
If this person were a "Muslim," he would say, "I am going to run to Muhammad; he is my shafi'."

351
00:34:12,099 --> 00:34:13,199
he is my intercessor.

352
00:34:21,359 --> 00:34:23,179
You have to believe in God alone.

353
00:34:27,920 --> 00:34:33,920
That day is going to come. See, this person leaves here on earth and forgets everything

354
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:39,880
he was doing. Now, and you are going to be like this person someday.

355
00:34:42,799 --> 00:34:50,840
You may not look this good by the way, but you do look very good, if you have this much

356
00:34:50,840 --> 00:34:51,059
faith.

357
00:34:55,920 --> 00:35:02,280
So you must, in order to stay on the path, you must... you must remember those awful situations that we will be in there.

358
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:03,599
situations that we will be in.

359
00:35:03,940 --> 00:35:07,460
And this is why God puts belief in the Hereafter next to belief in Him.

360
00:35:08,860 --> 00:35:11,019
Therefore, if you fall short, you cannot make it.

361
00:35:11,059 --> 00:35:12,840
You cannot just believe in God, or you will go to hell.

362
00:35:13,159 --> 00:35:14,480
You saw the slide.

363
00:35:15,280 --> 00:35:18,179
The majority of people who believe in God are going to hell.

364
00:35:18,519 --> 00:35:20,679
You must believe in God and the Hereafter.

365
00:35:25,900 --> 00:35:28,139
You must never neglect to feed your soul.

366
00:35:29,699 --> 00:35:31,559
Because this is what the battle is about, right?

367
00:35:31,840 --> 00:35:34,039
And people like myself, we've been grappling with it.

368
00:35:34,039 --> 00:35:41,900
Even, you know, that somebody in there might shout from there, "You know, I don't care for it, it's a garment that they throw away!"

369
00:35:42,880 --> 00:35:47,340
Remember your old clothes? You throw them away. What can you do with them now?

370
00:35:48,780 --> 00:35:53,639
Your body is just like that, old clothes, old garments.

371
00:35:56,319 --> 00:35:9,460
So, if you neglect to clean your clothes, it's your own fault.

372
00:36:02,880 --> 00:36:13,760
The five prayers are useless if you idolize anyone else besides God.

373
00:36:14,680 --> 00:36:18,059
God must be the only one, not number one.

374
00:36:18,400 --> 00:36:20,340
Because number one needs to have a number two.

375
00:36:21,500 --> 00:36:24,179
God must be the only one in your life.

376
00:36:27,960 --> 00:36:38,900
Allahummaghfir lil-mu'minina wal-mu'minat, wal-muslimina wal-muslimat, al-ahya'i minhum wal-amwat.
